parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Tire Feathering and Alignment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly align the front suspension and tires can cause uneven tire wear, leading to reduced traction and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Excessive tire noise
vibration
and uneven wear on the inside edge of the front tires
often resulting in the need for frequent tire replacements and alignments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive wear on the inside of the tires can cause loss of traction, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of tire blowouts, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Feathering or cupping on the inside of the tires
excessive tire noise
vibration
and pulling to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper alignment of the vehicle can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of tire blowouts, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Feathering or cupping on the inside of the tires
excessive tire noise
vibration
and pulling to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to notify customers and issue a recall can lead to continued use of defective vehicles, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: None
as this is a systemic issue rather than a vehicle-specific problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission grinds or makes a loud noise when shifting gears
the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of both the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the transmission grinds or makes a loud noise when shifting gears
the transmission hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut down without warning, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates

traction control light
